@simonexperiences Indeed! Ozone injection in gasoline combustion engines decomposes into pure Oxygen. 3 O³ => 6 O² 
It's a more powerful oxidizer than Nitrous Oxide but it hasn't become popular in cars due to Ozone's damage to rubber and the fact it spontaneously decomposes into Oxygen over time.
Ionized air can indeed improve combustion properties, partly because of the presence of Ozone.
